  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN192.1-kilavi">tōḻi talaimakaṉaic ceṟippu <app><lem>aṟivuṟīi</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3 #C7 #RK">aṟivuṟīi iravukkuṟi maṟuttatu</rdg></app> varaivu <app><lem>kaṭāyatu</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3 #RK">/</rdg></app>.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How the confidante urged for marriage by informing HIM of [her] confinement.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN192.1">
        <l>matiyirup paṉṉa mācaṟu cuṭarnutaṟ<anchor n="1"/></l>
        <l>poṉṉēr vaṇṇaṅ koṇṭaṉ ṟaṉṉō</l>
        <l>yāṅkā kuvaḷko ṟāṉē vicumpi</l>
        <l>ṉeyyā varivi laṉṉa paintārc</l>
        <l>cevvāyc ciṟukiḷi citaiya vāṅkip</l>
        <l>poṟaimelin tiṭṭa puṉpuṟap peruṅkural</l>
        <l>vaḷaiciṟai vāraṇaṅ kiḷaiyoṭu kavara</l>
        <l>vēṉalu miṟaṅkupoṟai yuyirttaṉa pāṉā</l>
        <l><supplied>ṇī</supplied>van ta<supplied>ḷi</supplied>kkuvai yeṉiṉē mālvarai</l>
        <l>maipaṭu viyalakan tuḻaii yoyyeṉa</l>
        <l>varuvi tanta varavumiḻ karumaṇi</l>
        <l>peruvaraic ciṟukuṭi maṟukuviḷak kuṟuttali</l>
        <l>ṉiravu miḻantaṉa ḷaḷiya ḷuravuppeya</l>
        <l>lurumiṟai koṇṭa vuyarcimaip</l>
        <l>perumalai nāṭaniṉ malarnta mārpē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>Like the seat of the moon, [her] flawless glowing forehead, (1)</l>
        <l>it has taken on a gold-like colour, alas. (2)</l>
        <l>What shall become of her? (3a-c)</l>
        <l>Bending over, to be spoilt by little parakeets with red beaks (5)</l>
        <l>[and] green garlands, like the striped bow in the sky that is not discharged, (3df.)</l>
        <l>as the curvy-winged fowl with [their] relatives seize (7)</l>
        <l>the low-backed big ears that are weakened under [their] burden, (6)</l>
        <l>all the millet [stalks] have begun to sigh under [their] inclining burden. (8a-c)</l>
        <l>If you say you will take care to come at midnight, (8d-9c)</l>
        <l>because the light of the black gem spit up by the snake, that was brought by the waterfall</l>
        <l>noisily stirring from within the shrouded width of the great mountain,</l>
        <l>falls on the streets of the little hamlet in the big mountains, (9d-12)</l>
        <l>she will have lost it at night too, pitiable she, (13a-c)</l>
        <l>– your blossoming chest, o man from a land of big mountains, (15)</l>
        <l>with high peaks that strong rain [and] thunder take as [their] seat. (13df.)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>

